		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Thanks! <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> <br /><br />I suspect that counting the weeks like that is somewhat local, though. For example this is manifested in lighting 4 candles in cascade/cumulatively; 1 more lit each sunday: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://images.styleroom.se/image/scaled/huge/x1su/1/196363-adventsljusstake.jpg">https://images.styleroom.se/image/scale ... sstake.jpg</a><!-- m --><br /><br />When i studied ethnography, a seminar was about 19th century's changed/digitized perception of time, what with railroads and mechanized clocks having an increasing impact. Apparently this was also the time when the celebration of advent took fire; not least as a method to train the patience of children with fun little rituals.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Ooze</div><br />something like that, yes  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_mrgreen.gif" alt=":mrgreen:" title="Mr. Green" />

		

